  "prompt": "How many grafts are needed to get a full beard by facial hair transplant? How much will it cost in India?",
  "response": "The number of grafts needed for a full beard transplant can vary significantly based on individual factors such as the desired density, the area to be covered, and the existing facial hair. On average, a beard transplant may require anywhere from 1,500 to 3,000 grafts to achieve a satisfactory fullness and coverage. \n\nIn India, the cost for a beard transplant typically ranges from \u20b930,000 to \u20b91,00,000 (approximately $400 to $1,300 USD) depending on the clinic, the experience of the surgeon, and the number of grafts required. It's advisable to consult with a specialized clinic to get a personalized assessment and estimate based on your specific needs. Always ensure that the clinic follows proper safety and hygiene standards.",
